      "span_text": "In the field of on-patient medical data visualization, the Contextual Anatomic Mimesis proposed in [CITATION_1] controls the visualization by using three parameters: curvature of the patient's skin surface, angle of incidence factor (i.e. angle between the normal on the skin surface and a vector pointing from the position of the surface and the eye) and distance falloff (i.e. distance between each point on the surface and the intersection point of the line of sight and the skin surface).",
